when I was a child,

00:04:50.460 --> 00:04:51.920
there was no television.

00:04:51.920 --> 00:04:55.370
Obviously, there
were no computers,

00:04:55.370 --> 00:04:58.180
and there were no
mobile telephones.

00:04:58.180 --> 00:05:04.490
And so the only source of
entertainment was radio.

00:05:04.490 --> 00:05:10.730
And I think the first
influence during those years

00:05:10.730 --> 00:05:16.790
was Begum Akhtar, the
famous ghazal singer,

00:05:16.790 --> 00:05:18.560
I used to listen to--

00:05:18.560 --> 00:05:21.800
I was quite intrigued because
I was too small to figure out

00:05:21.800 --> 00:05:24.800
as to who she was,
what she sang,

00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:29.840
but her voice and her style
really appealed to me.

00:05:29.840 --> 00:05:34.580
And then slowly,
I inquired and I

00:05:34.580 --> 00:05:38.790
got to know that she
was India's pride,

00:05:38.790 --> 00:05:45.080
and she was the first lady who
popularized this form of music,

00:05:45.080 --> 00:05:46.730
which is ghazal.

00:05:46.730 --> 00:05:50.840
And she had peculiar voice.

00:05:50.840 --> 00:05:53.540
Her voice was very,
very different

00:05:53.540 --> 00:05:57.230
than the normal female
voices, so it really

00:05:57.230 --> 00:06:00.440
suited this kind of singing.

00:06:00.440 --> 00:06:06.510
And I guess that
impression lasted forever.

00:06:06.510 --> 00:06:09.860
And I think that that
was my initiation

00:06:09.860 --> 00:06:12.680
into ghazal singing that was--

00:06:12.680 --> 00:06:15.830
that's when I got inspired.

00:06:15.830 --> 00:06:21.290
And then I started following
this form of music religiously.

00:06:21.290 --> 00:06:25.970
And then, obviously, came
the issue of language,

00:06:25.970 --> 00:06:28.910
because ghazal, as
you know, basically--

00:06:28.910 --> 00:06:31.940
the medium, the
language is Urdu.

00:06:31.940 --> 00:06:36.770
And it was, again, a coincidence
that my eldest brother, Manhar

00:06:36.770 --> 00:06:41.030
Udhas, was a very
famous playback singer.

00:06:41.030 --> 00:06:48.050
Manharji was learning Urdu
from a very, very renowned Urdu

00:06:48.050 --> 00:06:49.700
teacher.

00:06:49.700 --> 00:06:52.130
Manharji was learning
only because he

00:06:52.130 --> 00:06:54.560
was pursuing playback
singing, and he

00:06:54.560 --> 00:07:01.250
wanted to really make
his diction very refined,

00:07:01.250 --> 00:07:06.140
and he wanted to make sure that
whatever he sang was perfect.

00:07:06.140 --> 00:07:10.070
So for that, he
was learning Urdu.

00:07:10.070 --> 00:07:15.680
And it was his teacher who
actually really inspired

00:07:15.680 --> 00:07:17.990
me, who really, in
fact, impressed me.

00:07:17.990 --> 00:07:21.100
And one fine day, with
a lot of hesitation,

00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:27.410
I gathered courage to ask him
if he could teach me Urdu.

00:07:27.410 --> 00:07:29.660
And he readily agreed.

00:07:29.660 --> 00:07:31.310
He said yes.

00:07:31.310 --> 00:07:34.540
